      • emptyIterable

        public static <T> Iterable<T> emptyIterable()
        Returns the empty Iterable for a particular type (type-safe). Note that unlike this method, the like-named static field does not provide type safety.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the Iterable's elements.
        Returns:
        the empty Iterable.

      • concat

        public static <T> Iterable<T> concat(Iterable<? extends T>... iterables)
        Concatenates the given Iterables into a single one. Note that the returned Iterable is only a view, that is, any subsequent update on any of the input Iterables will affect the returned view. The input Iterables will not be polled until necessary. The returned view's Iterator supports Iterator.remove() when the corresponding input Iterator supports it.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the returned Iterables' elements.
        Parameters:
        iterables - the Iterables to concatenate.
        Returns:
        the concatenated Iterable.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if iterables is null or if it contains a null reference.

      • cycle

        public static <T> Iterable<T> cycle(Iterable<? extends T> iterable)
        Returns a cyclic Iterable that cycles indefinitely over the given Iterable's elements. The returned Iterable's Iterator supports Iterator#remove().
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the returned Iterable's elements.
        Parameters:
        iterable - the Iterable containing the elements to cycle over.
        Returns:
        the cyclic Iterable.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if iterable is null.

      • limit

        public static <T> Iterable<T> limit(Iterable<? extends T> iterable,
                                    int limit)
        Returns an Iterable view of the given Iterable that will only return its first limit items. The returned view's Iterators support Iterator.remove() if the original Iterator does.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the returned Iterable's elements.
        Parameters:
        iterable - the Iterable to limit.
        limit - the number of elements in the returned Iterable.
        Returns:
        the limited Iterable.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if iterable is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - if (limit is negative.

      • skip

        public static <T> Iterable<T> skip(Iterable<T> iterable,
                                   int n)
        Returns an Iterable view of the given Iterable that skips its first n elements. The returned Iterable's Iterator supports Iterator.remove() if the original Iterator does.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the Iterable's elements.
        Parameters:
        iterable - the input Iterable.
        n - the number of items to skip.
        Returns:
        the skipping Iterable.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if iterable is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - if (n is negative.
